A mugger was thwarted and jailed thanks to two postal workers who chased him through the streets after hearing his victim's cries for help.

Drug addict Daniel Hall, 33, snatched a woman's bag after she got off a bus in Plymouth, Devon.

But the 42-year-old victim's cries were heard by Royal Mail workers Martin Harris, 49, and Sharon O'Connor, 38, who were driving past in their mail van.

