They chased up with the thief, who flung down the bag before making his escape. He was arrested just a few hours later because of the detailed   description the two postal workers gave police.

The father-of-one, who has more than 29 previous convictions, began an eight month jail sentence this week after admitting robbery at Plymouth Crown   Court.

Mr Harris and Ms O'Connor described how they were doing their morning round on January 30 when they heard the victim shouting for help.

